tion and as a way to privatize it ocp intended to give something back to the city and shared a contract to run local law enforcement their projects included ed robocop and robocop  ocp owns and operates a privatized detroit police department and have been known to secretly work with criminals to achieve their goals however the city owed them  millions and as a result ocp cut the salary of the police officers to  as the old man explained to mayor marvin kuzak that the debt was in ocps favor in the event of default ocp shall have the uncontested right of foreclosure on all city assets kanemitsu takeoveredit ocp was eventually bought by a japanese zaibutsu the kanemitsu corporation as a kanemitsu subsidiary ocp remains in charge of the destruction of old detroit and the construction of delta city by the end of the movie ocps brutal policies concerning delta city are brought to light many of ocps majority shareholders sell their stock and ocp itself is forced into bankruptcy ocp was shut down and went bankrupt for good after robocop  by the time of robocop prime directives ocp is shown being manipulated by a brash young executive who through murder and reallocation of resources ascends to power to automate delta city under a new artificial intelligence called saint this is manipulated by the cyberterrorist david kaydick who seeks the destruction of the human race through a virus called legion that can be introduced to computers and human beings alike in a flashback robocop remembers working with john cable during the conversation cable claims that detroit is a cesspit and murphy suggests well maybe this whole ocp thingll do some good get some more money in the department some more cops on the street to which john replies you really wanna trust your life to a conglomerate murphy what a smart man this series ignores robocop  and  this is why ocp is still around and not bankrupt like at the end of robocop  ocp from prime directives is an alternate reality from robocop has nothing do with robocop  or  divisionsedit lowe technologies mediabreakmedianet security concepts urban rehabilitators known executivesedit robocop  robocop edit the old man the ceo of ocp—or as he is known by his employees the old man—appears in robocop  film and robocop  sharing his dream of privatizing old detroit into a utopia dubbed delta city richard dick jones ocps senior president and the main antagonist in the first film jones developed the ed robot to reduce crime in old detroit but it all went horribly wrong when the android malfunctioned and killed a volunteer for the demonstration he has secret ties to the ruthless crime boss clarence boddicker donald johnson mortons partner in the robocop program he appears in robocop and robocop  in a supporting role he has a good head for business making some good suggestions but seems slightly unsure of the way ocp does business robert bob morton a young and arrogant officer of ocp who uses the above incident in the boardroom as an opportunity for his robocop project much to joness dismay his only appearance was in the first robocop film midway in the film he was killed by his rival through copkiller clarence boddicker doctor juliette faxx robocop edit the ceo the new boss of ocp who under orders from the kanemitsu zaibatsu must have detroit gone in order to make way for delta city he appears to be more aggressive than the previous ceo as he fires one of the employees for insulting the big boss donald johnson johnson is still working for ocp but obviously just doesnt have what it takes to get to the top he is now ocps senior vice president he does threaten sgt warren reed near the end of the movie implying that reed would lose his job if he didnt join the rehabs this is one of his darker moments had ocp continued he may have been ceo one day jeff fleck the apparent head of security concepts after having his ass chewed by the ceo he pays a visit to dr marie lazarus and robocop he decides that robocop should not have the right to make a choice and wants his emotions removed later on he is fired for talking badly about the kanemitsu corporation in front of otomo while the ceo is briefing him as he had explained to johnson earlier he left the room pulling a gun from his jacket to commit suicide a gun shot is heard paul mcdaggett robocop the seriesedit the chairman the ceo of ocp appears in robocop the series he is a more humane version of the old man from the original movies during the series he learns lessons from robocop and diana chip chayken vice president of ocp in robocop the series in many ways similar to dick jones of the original movies he was known to the police as the dog town ripper although they were unaware of his identity at the time he used this name while hunting down homeless people and harvesting their brains for dr cray mallardo and his neurobrain project aubrey fox robocop prime directivesedit  serve the public trust  protect the innocent  uphold the law  classified cannot arrest an active ocp executive chairwoman damian lowe sara cable retrieved from httprobocopwikiacomwikiomniconsumerproductsoldid ad blocker interference detected wikia is a freetouse site that makes money from advertising we have a modified experience for viewers using ad blockers wikia is not accessible if you’ve made further modifications remove the custom ad blocker rules and the page will load as expected transformers summer scifi morrowind top  people directory people directory advertisements people profiles trending over the last  hours anna galland berkeley ca companies moveonorg political action sydney b simpson saint petersburg fl companies simpsy llc robert h dunlap batesville ms companies hesselbein tire southwest inc hesselbein tire co inc gateway tire of texas inc amy narcisco union city ca companies aen homes llc majid hemmasi austin tx companies central texas fire  safety equipment inc aaa fire  safety equipment co inc drfm investments inc richard foote lubbock tx companies fired up holding company inc joseph walter hertel rocklin ca companies armstrong  getty entormation llc michael mcqueen lenoir nc companies phoenix worldwide logistics inc phoenix worldwide inc pw energy services inc thomas n chieffe chagrin falls oh companies dayton superior corporation ralph holguin bellflower ca companies rmd support connection inc rmd group inc rmd garage llc people directory names starting with letters a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z you must be signed in to print once signed in look for the pdf button unisonic products corporation  wikipedia unisonic products corporation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search industry consumer electronics headquarters united states products calculators crt television sets video game consoles digital watches telephones answering machines digital watches alarm clocks unisonic products corporation was an american manufacturer and distributor of consumer electronics from the s to the s although headquartered in new york city unisonic outsourced its manufacturing operations to various facilities in east asia especially in hong kong south korea and japan unisonic developed a variety of electronics including calculators crt television sets video game consoles digital watches telephones answering machines and digital alarm clocks in  franklin electronic publishers sued unisonic products corporation for misleading advertising contents  electronic game calculators  foray into the video game console market  see also  notes  references electronic game calculatorsedit in the late s and early s unisonic released a series of digital calculators that featured a quartz clock and an electronic game among the calculators produced were casino  and mickey mouse space quiz model number fs both released in  and  model number pb which was released in  and featured a blackjack game casino  and  each employed a vacuum fluorescent display vfd whereas mickey mouse space quiz used two lightemitting diodes leds one green and one red to indicate correct and incorrect quiz answers respectively foray into the video game console marketedit like dozens of other manufacturers of consumer electronics unisonic released a series of dedicated consoles in the late s the consoles were generally patterned on home pong a game console released by atari inc in  unisonic released its first console in  the unisonic sportsman t which featured four selectable games two linear paddle controllers and a light gun unisonic followed the sportsman with a series of variations through  and  all for the us market as was the case with most pong clones of the s unisonics sportsman and tournament consoles were driven by general instruments ay an integrated circuit containing seven video games the unisonic consoles models not featuring a light gun offered a subset of these consisting of four games practice squash hockey and tennis the tournament  was the first unisonic console equipped with the light gun accessory and with it unisonic introduced two additional games skeet and target in  the company released its last pong console the olympian  which featured ten games and substituted joysticks for the paddle controllers and light gun it is based on the ay pong chip with the addition of colors thanks to the ay in  the company released the champion  console based on a real cpu the cp used also by the intellivision differently from the intellivision that use the gimini full range  programmable game set for sound and video it uses the ay chip that is a lot less powerful the games are only textual it had  games builtin and a cartridge slot only  cartridges are known the system was produced in very low quantities and now is extremely rare the console is the only one known to use the gimini mid range  programmable game set as described in the gimini products book the  had been later renamed in  the console has been emulated by mame emulator the console was also sold in japan with the name casino tv games at the start of  atari inc which released the atari video computer system in north america some months prior to the olympian s street date went on to dominate the video game console market in north america until the north american video game crash of  model name model number serial numbers year of release number of selectable games light gun manufactured in chip sportsman t t    no hong kong ay tournament  t    no hong kong ay tournament  t    no hong kong  players may be the mps tournament  t    yes hong kong ay tournament      no hong kong ay tournament  t    no hong kong ay tournament  tjr    yes japan ay tournament      yes  ay olympian      yes japan ay ayadd colors champion    builtin  cartridge no cpcpu ayvideo and sound see alsoedit telstar game console nelsonic industries notesedit  archived copy archived from the original on july   retrieved april     httpmycalcdbfreefrmainphplb  a b c httpwwwccjvqcomslydcindexfaq  archived copy pdf archived from the original pdf on march   retrieved november     httpforumsbannisterorgubbthreadsphpubbshowflatnumberpage  httpwwwcomputerhistoryorgcollectionsaccessionx  httpwwwcomputerhistoryorgcollectionsaccession referencesedit the farmers character and advertising phones – m – features two mickey mouse telephones manufactured by unisonic in  and  respectively accessed on  april  pong picture page accessed on  april  table of pong consoles and clones from pongstorycom accessed on  april  pong the video game by atari inc from arcadehistorycom accessed on  april  pong in a chip from pongstorycom accessed on  april  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleunisonicproductscorporationoldid categories companies based in new york cityelectronics companies of the united statesvideo game companies of the united stateswatch brandshidden categories pages using deprecated image syntax navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view his